laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild atelectasis at the lung bases. The liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions. Patent portal venous system. No intra or extrahepatic biliary duct dilation. Normal gallbladder without gallstones. Unremarkable spleen and adrenal glands. Normal pancreas without focal lesions. Symmetric renal nephrograms with contrast excretion and no focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis. Normal ureters. Normal distal esophagus and grossly unremarkable stomach. Small and large bowel normal in caliber without wall thickening. Mild dilation of the distal appendix measuring 12 mm with minimal adjacent fat stranding. No extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection. No cecal thickening. Abdominal aorta and branches patent. Normal pelvic bladder and no pelvic fluid. Follicular activity noted in both ovaries. No focal lytic or sclerotic lesions in osseous structures.
